Kenya Basketball Federation assistant secretary Ambrose Kisoi, in a circular reiterated that all branches and commissions should elect new officials who will run their affairs for the next four years by January 4According to Kisoi, branches, commissions and teams are required to send names of two delegates who will participate in the national polls by January 11The calendar of events also include the Africa Women’s Club Championships in March where Kenya teams Kenya Ports Authority and Equity Bank are expected to take part, the Anoca Youth games set for Cairo in April and men's Afrobasket final tour set for Rwanda in August Elections are top of this year's Kenya Basketball Federation's calendar of events which start with the branches and commissions on Monday.
Kenya Basketball Federation assistant secretary Ambrose Kisoi, in a circular reiterated that all branches and commissions should elect new officials who will run their affairs for the next four years by January 4 so that two delegates can be forwarded to the national elections slated for January 23.



